TZANEEN - President Cyril Ramaphosa got into the groove of things on Saturday, doing the newly coined "Ramajive". Ramaphoza was addressing a celebration marking the recognition of the Queenship status of the Balobedu tribe. READ: Balobedu rain queen returns Ramaphosa, who has been advocating for people to have a healthy, active lifestyle, did not hold back when he found himself in the middle of the dancing part of the celebration. eNCA